Variables :
---1)Static typed and Dynamic typed:
1)Variables 
2)Variables are used to store the data (any kind of data)

Variables:
1)Case-sensitive 
2)start with letters , _  (under_score)  , $ (dollarsign)
3)cant start with numbers
4)Reserved words (keywords) not allowed
5)Allow  letters , _ (under_score)  , $ (dollarsign) , numbers

How to declare variables:
	var
	let
	const

1)Var keyword  1995-2015
2)let keyword  2015
3)var used only old browsers

1)Reassigning variables is possible by var
1)Reassigning  variables :

 var fav_std="ramya"
     fav_std="kavya"
     fav_std="sam"
     document.write(fav_std)
     console.log(fav_std)

Output: sam
Example:2
 var a=1;
   a=5;
   document.write(a+a)
   console.log(a+a)
Output: 10



1)Reassigning variables is possible by var
2)Reassigning  with let also accepted
3) Reassigning  with const not accepted


Redeclaring with var is accepted :
Example:
   var a=1;
   var a=5;
   document.write(a+a)
   console.log(a+a)

Output : 10

Redeclaring with let is not accepted :
Example:
 let a=1;
   let a=5;
   document.write(a+a)
   console.log(a+a)

Output : error

	Redeclaring with var is accepted :
	Redeclaring with let is not accepted :
	Redeclaring with const is not accepted :

Block scope:
Variables  declared with  var doesnot have block scope
var a="sai"
{
    var a="kumar"
    console.log(a)
}
console.log(a)

variables declared with let have block scope



